WEBVTT

00:02.670 --> 00:03.830
Previously on
"Marvel's Inhumans"...

00:03.830 --> 00:04.880
We'll complete the mission
King Maximus gave us.

00:04.880 --> 00:05.960
We'll hold
these pitiful humans hostage

00:05.960 --> 00:07.290
and force Black Bolt
to come to us.

00:07.290 --> 00:08.960
[ Engine revving,
Lockjaw yelps ]

00:08.960 --> 00:09.710
Lockjaw!

00:09.710 --> 00:10.830
He needs a doctor.

00:10.830 --> 00:11.920
Yeah, my friend,
she's a vet.

00:11.920 --> 00:13.210
Why do you two
hate each other?

00:13.210 --> 00:14.960
'Cause we just broke up.

00:14.960 --> 00:16.080
We need your assistance

00:16.080 --> 00:18.170
to take down
the false king of Attilan.

00:18.170 --> 00:19.380
Isn't this
Bronaja's father?

00:19.380 --> 00:21.170
He was also the only one
who considered it an honor

00:21.170 --> 00:22.880
to be drafted
into your army.

00:22.880 --> 00:24.830
Some Inhumans might wonder

00:24.830 --> 00:26.380
if this is for the good
of Attilan...

00:26.380 --> 00:27.880
or for the good
of Maximus.

00:27.880 --> 00:29.000
This is a fatal wound.

00:29.000 --> 00:30.420
Crystal's here.
Where is she?

00:30.420 --> 00:33.080
Please...
be the king we deserve.

00:33.080 --> 00:33.830
♪♪

00:44.000 --> 00:50.170
♪♪

00:50.170 --> 00:52.380
[ Gasps ]

00:52.380 --> 00:56.880
Black Bolt, wait.

00:56.880 --> 00:59.460
I-I didn't mean
for this to happen.

00:59.460 --> 01:01.920
Yet it did.

01:01.920 --> 01:06.750
I was hoping for
a peaceful transition of power.

01:06.750 --> 01:07.790
Things got out of hand.

01:07.790 --> 01:09.000
You killed Triton.

01:09.000 --> 01:11.250
And now we kill you.

01:11.250 --> 01:13.500
Brother, please...

01:13.500 --> 01:15.460
He's not too pleased
to be your brother.

01:15.460 --> 01:18.380
He knows you were the one
who killed your parents.

01:18.380 --> 01:19.460
That's not true.

01:19.460 --> 01:21.330
♪♪

01:21.330 --> 01:23.120
[ Shuddered breathing ]

01:23.120 --> 01:25.000
[ Inhales sharply ]

01:25.000 --> 01:27.670
[ Gasps ]

01:27.670 --> 01:36.040
♪♪

01:36.040 --> 01:43.040
♪♪

01:46.710 --> 01:48.290
[ Lockjaw grunts ]

01:48.290 --> 01:50.460
His side's
all swollen again.

01:50.460 --> 01:52.330
What have you been doing
with him?

01:52.330 --> 01:54.920
Nothing. He's just
been teleporting us around.

01:54.920 --> 01:56.040
Well...

01:57.880 --> 01:59.210
...don't do that anymore.

01:59.210 --> 02:00.580
It's made him a lot worse.

02:00.580 --> 02:02.750
I know my dog.
He's gonna be fine.

02:02.750 --> 02:03.790
Aren't you, baby?

02:03.790 --> 02:05.830
He needs rest.

02:05.830 --> 02:07.790
[ Lockjaw panting ]

02:07.790 --> 02:09.790
[ Door opens ]
You should take him home.

02:09.790 --> 02:12.830
You should both go home,
wherever that is.

02:12.830 --> 02:14.880
I'm not leaving
without my family.

02:14.880 --> 02:16.210
Well, how many are you?

02:16.210 --> 02:18.120
Shouldn't you be
on a register or something?

02:18.120 --> 02:19.880
I don't know
what you're talking about.

02:19.880 --> 02:21.420
I'm gonna make sure
they have a picture of you.

02:21.420 --> 02:22.880
What are you doing?
Audrey, don't.

02:22.880 --> 02:24.040
Aah!

02:24.040 --> 02:28.000
♪♪

02:28.000 --> 02:29.920
I'm not afraid of you.

02:29.920 --> 02:30.920
♪♪

02:30.920 --> 02:32.960
You should be.

02:32.960 --> 02:35.620
This isn't over.

02:35.620 --> 02:38.540
♪♪

02:38.540 --> 02:40.460
You should know,

02:40.460 --> 02:42.380
when Audrey says
something's not over,

02:42.380 --> 02:44.460
it's not over.

02:44.460 --> 02:45.880
She's right, though.

02:45.880 --> 02:47.580
We wore out Lockjaw.

02:48.830 --> 02:52.330
I don't know what to do.
I have to find my family now.

02:52.330 --> 02:53.790
Okay. Well, let's --
let's think.

02:53.790 --> 02:56.210
I've seen you do
all kinds of crazy things.

02:56.210 --> 02:57.920
I've seen the wind thing

02:57.920 --> 03:00.460
and now balls of fire
or whatever that was.

03:00.460 --> 03:02.290
Is there anything
you can't control?

03:02.290 --> 03:04.920
I control the elements.
That's my gift.

03:04.920 --> 03:06.420
[ Chuckles ] Okay.

03:06.420 --> 03:08.880
So maybe you could create
a forest fire or a water spout

03:08.880 --> 03:10.170
or something like that?

03:10.170 --> 03:13.080
Yeah, I guess, but why
would I want to do that?

03:13.080 --> 03:14.960
♪♪

03:14.960 --> 03:17.670
I can send my family a signal --
that I'm here.

03:17.670 --> 03:19.120
Exactly.

03:19.120 --> 03:20.920
Lightning.
I'll create lightning!

03:20.920 --> 03:22.000
They can trace it
right to me.

03:22.000 --> 03:23.210
Wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait!

03:23.210 --> 03:25.750
Uh, maybe let's not do that
right here.

03:25.750 --> 03:27.790
I don't want
to burn down the barn.

03:27.790 --> 03:30.500
We should go up somewhere high
so they can see it.

03:30.500 --> 03:32.000
Yeah, yeah, hop in.

03:32.000 --> 03:34.040
Medusa: We need to find Crystal
as soon as possible.

03:34.040 --> 03:36.120
Karnak: Yes, but without Locus,
how do we do that?

03:36.120 --> 03:38.330
Hey, how did you find us?

03:38.330 --> 03:40.580
Uh, you left
very distinct energy bursts

03:40.580 --> 03:43.750
when you guys landed
in Hawaii...

03:43.750 --> 03:45.540
[ Insects chirping ]

03:45.540 --> 03:48.460
Then Crystal would've left
a sign, as well.

03:48.460 --> 03:50.080
You know what?
Just give me a minute.

03:50.080 --> 03:51.710
Give me a minute.

03:51.710 --> 03:53.790
Do we have a plan for
once we get back up there?

03:53.790 --> 03:55.750
Maximus has
the Royal Guards.

03:55.750 --> 03:59.080
I'm not sure...I'm the one
who should come up with a plan.

03:59.080 --> 04:02.420
My mind is...not as reliable
as in the past.

04:02.420 --> 04:04.380
I say we go in there running
and screaming

04:04.380 --> 04:05.620
and tear them all
to shreds.

04:05.620 --> 04:07.620
And I say we give Karnak
a little more time.

04:07.620 --> 04:09.670
[ Insects chirping ]

04:19.580 --> 04:21.120
What'd he say?

04:21.120 --> 04:23.080
♪♪

04:23.080 --> 04:25.040
He said
we need to take down Maximus,

04:25.040 --> 04:27.670
but what he means by
"take down,"

04:27.670 --> 04:29.500
I'm not exactly sure.

04:29.500 --> 04:30.830
I know I said we needed
to throw Maximus

04:30.830 --> 04:32.080
off the highest wall
in Attilan,

04:32.080 --> 04:34.170
but I think...

04:34.170 --> 04:36.670
I think we need
to take him alive.

04:36.670 --> 04:38.500
Then let me smash his head in
in front of the whole city.

04:38.500 --> 04:40.500
Gorgon, I love you,
but you are not helping.

04:40.500 --> 04:47.420
♪♪

04:47.420 --> 04:50.170
Haven't we learned anything
from my parents?

04:50.170 --> 04:53.670
Yep, yeah, yes, yes.
There...

04:53.670 --> 04:55.040
There was another one.

04:55.040 --> 04:57.750
Uh, it -- it came in
after you guys already landed.

04:57.750 --> 05:00.380
It looks like it's on the, uh,
the northern part of the island.

05:00.380 --> 05:02.420
So let's find her.

05:02.420 --> 05:03.620
[ Vibrating ]
Hold on.

05:03.620 --> 05:05.040
You're vibrating.

05:05.040 --> 05:06.960
♪♪

05:06.960 --> 05:10.080
It, uh -- It's just --
It's Locus' comlink.

05:10.080 --> 05:11.580
I thought this was broken.

05:11.580 --> 05:13.830
I -- I -- I've been,
uh...tinkering with it.

05:13.830 --> 05:15.170
I'm a bit of a tinkerer.

05:15.170 --> 05:16.460
It's just --
It's a habit that I have.

05:16.460 --> 05:18.420
[ Comlink beeps ]
Auran.

05:18.420 --> 05:21.790
Auran: Medusa. I hope
you're enjoying your reunion.

05:21.790 --> 05:24.210
What do you want?

05:24.210 --> 05:26.040
I'm curious
if Black Bolt still has

05:26.040 --> 05:28.000
that frankly
disgusting fondness

05:28.000 --> 05:30.620
for his human friends
Declan and Sammy.

05:32.380 --> 05:33.750
He wants to know
what you've done with them.

05:33.750 --> 05:35.040
Nothing yet.

05:35.040 --> 05:36.710
But if you and Black Bolt
don't come back for them,

05:36.710 --> 05:38.170
they will die.

05:38.170 --> 05:40.500
Using hostages
is a new low for you, Auran.

05:40.500 --> 05:41.920
Gorgon used to tell us

05:41.920 --> 05:44.120
there was nothing more important
than the mission.

05:44.120 --> 05:46.210
This isn't necessary.
We've only tried to help.

05:46.210 --> 05:48.420
Oh. Your voice
is so adorable.

05:48.420 --> 05:50.750
Medusa: So you think we're just
gonna walk right into your trap?

05:50.750 --> 05:52.620
Up to you.

05:52.620 --> 05:58.670
♪♪

05:58.670 --> 06:00.040
Say we wanted to meet up.

06:00.040 --> 06:01.830
How would we do that?

06:01.830 --> 06:03.420
You have Locus.

06:03.420 --> 06:05.620
♪♪

06:05.620 --> 06:07.120
I'm sorry.

06:07.120 --> 06:09.080
We don't.
Locus is dead.

06:09.080 --> 06:11.420
♪♪

06:11.420 --> 06:13.210
We haven't gone anywhere.
We're still at the lab.

06:13.210 --> 06:15.170
[ Comlink beeps ]

06:15.170 --> 06:18.670
♪♪

06:18.670 --> 06:20.960
Who are Declan and Sammy?

06:20.960 --> 06:22.500
Friends of Black Bolt.

06:22.500 --> 06:25.290
Even so,
Crystal is our priority.

06:25.290 --> 06:27.750
We don't know what danger
she might be in.

06:27.750 --> 06:29.750
Going to rescue those two
sounds off-mission.

06:29.750 --> 06:33.170
Hey, this is Hawaii,

06:33.170 --> 06:34.960
and I know
how people act here.

06:34.960 --> 06:36.750
We help our friends.

06:36.750 --> 06:38.710
But most importantly, I want to
rip the head off of Auran.

06:38.710 --> 06:40.380
Vengeance
is not gonna help.

06:40.380 --> 06:42.880
He's probably right, though.
Auran's not gonna disappear.

06:42.880 --> 06:44.250
If we don't
deal with her now,

06:44.250 --> 06:45.670
we'll just have to
deal with her later.

06:45.670 --> 06:46.920
♪♪

06:50.580 --> 06:52.880
He says he wants the two of you
to go after the humans

06:52.880 --> 06:54.460
while him and I
find Crystal.

06:54.460 --> 06:57.500
Is -- Is separating
a good idea?

06:57.500 --> 06:58.880
We're at our best when...

07:02.460 --> 07:05.330
We need to find Crystal
and return to Attilan,

07:05.330 --> 07:07.080
and then...

07:07.080 --> 07:11.250
and then
we can tend to Maximus.

07:11.250 --> 07:14.710
Facing Auran, I'm --
I'm not sure I'm ready

07:14.710 --> 07:17.420
for a big fight.

07:17.420 --> 07:19.830
Karnak...

07:19.830 --> 07:21.830
even at half
your strength,

07:21.830 --> 07:23.960
you are Attilan's
greatest fighter.

07:25.170 --> 07:27.620
Second-best, I guess.

07:27.620 --> 07:29.830
♪♪

07:29.830 --> 07:31.580
Thank you, my Queen.

07:31.580 --> 07:33.500
I'm in.

07:33.500 --> 07:36.080
Good. Thank you.

07:36.080 --> 07:37.960
♪♪

07:37.960 --> 07:39.540
So, where's this lab?

07:39.540 --> 07:41.380
Louise: Follow this road east
for about a mile.

07:41.380 --> 07:43.080
So we better
get going, then.

07:43.080 --> 07:44.380
-Right.
-Okay.

07:44.380 --> 07:45.710
As soon as we find Crystal
and Lockjaw,

07:45.710 --> 07:46.670
we'll come back for you.

07:46.670 --> 07:49.750
♪♪

07:49.750 --> 07:51.750
[ Engine starts ]

07:51.750 --> 07:55.250
[ Vehicle departs ]

07:55.250 --> 07:56.420
♪♪

07:56.420 --> 07:58.880
This is
a great moment, son.

07:58.880 --> 08:00.290
It's a chance
to finally prove ourselves.

08:00.290 --> 08:01.620
But you could die.

08:01.620 --> 08:04.210
It would be an honor
to die for freedom and Attilan.

08:04.210 --> 08:06.170
Father, how long
have you trained for this?

08:06.170 --> 08:07.670
A day?

08:07.670 --> 08:10.790
Bronaja, don't worry, son.

08:10.790 --> 08:14.250
I'm coming back a free man.

08:14.250 --> 08:17.040
♪♪

08:17.040 --> 08:19.460
Maximus: Look at you.

08:19.460 --> 08:23.580
Inhumans formerly cast off,
hidden away,

08:23.580 --> 08:24.920
now on the front line

08:24.920 --> 08:27.170
of the battle
for our very existence.

08:27.170 --> 08:31.670
Black Bolt, all the while,
is planning, scheming,

08:31.670 --> 08:33.620
trying to find a way
to take back Attilan

08:33.620 --> 08:37.290
and bring back
the decayed caste system.

08:37.290 --> 08:40.250
Auran and her brave soldiers
need your help

08:40.250 --> 08:42.210
to capture Black Bolt
and the others

08:42.210 --> 08:43.580
before they steal back
the throne

08:43.580 --> 08:46.040
and send you back
to the mines.

08:46.040 --> 08:47.960
Are you up to the task?

08:47.960 --> 08:49.830
-Yes, my King.
-Yes, my King.

08:49.830 --> 08:52.750
The very best
Attilan has to offer.

08:52.750 --> 08:55.540
♪♪

08:55.540 --> 08:57.120
You should be proud
of your father.

08:57.120 --> 09:00.000
His loyalty is unshakeable.

09:00.000 --> 09:03.790
He is an example
for all of us.

09:03.790 --> 09:07.080
Eldrac, are you ready?

09:07.080 --> 09:10.120
[ Echoing ] That's
a lot of people.

09:10.120 --> 09:11.540
♪♪

09:11.540 --> 09:14.170
Step forward, my warriors.

09:14.170 --> 09:25.080
♪♪

09:25.080 --> 09:26.920
What will the people think

09:26.920 --> 09:30.960
when they find out
you sent miners to war?

09:30.960 --> 09:34.500
They're honored that
I treat them as equal.

09:34.500 --> 09:38.380
The people love me.
They'll do anything for me.

09:38.380 --> 09:40.080
Yes, my King.

09:40.080 --> 09:42.620
♪♪

09:42.620 --> 09:44.580
And if Black Bolt
obliterates them all,

09:44.580 --> 09:46.670
well, then,

09:46.670 --> 09:47.790
that'll make
the rest of our citizens

09:47.790 --> 09:48.920
hate him all the more.

09:48.920 --> 09:56.710
♪♪

09:56.710 --> 09:58.880
[ Insects chirping ]

10:11.960 --> 10:13.920
-Beautiful.
-Mm.

10:13.920 --> 10:15.580
I had no idea.

10:15.580 --> 10:17.580
Yeah, grass is green,
the flowers are bright,

10:17.580 --> 10:18.710
the birds sing so pretty.

10:18.710 --> 10:21.210
You're soldiers,
not tourists!

10:21.210 --> 10:23.960
We're proud
to be of service.

10:23.960 --> 10:25.170
Good.

10:25.170 --> 10:27.170
Let's go.

10:27.170 --> 10:29.540
Behind me.

10:29.540 --> 10:34.500
♪♪

10:34.500 --> 10:36.420
He's becoming
more paranoid.

10:36.420 --> 10:38.420
Every hour, he surrounds
himself with more guards.

10:38.420 --> 10:39.830
I'm not sure
what I can do.

10:39.830 --> 10:41.170
Well, we've got to
get him alone.

10:41.170 --> 10:44.000
-How?
-I'll find a way.

10:44.000 --> 10:45.920
Perhaps we should wait.

10:45.920 --> 10:49.420
No, assemble your team.
Get anyone loyal to Black Bolt.

10:49.420 --> 10:51.920
He's sending us off to Earth
to die one by one.

10:51.920 --> 10:54.000
If we don't act soon,
there won't be any of us left.

10:54.000 --> 10:56.670
Maximus must die.

10:56.670 --> 11:02.120
♪♪

11:09.120 --> 11:10.330
Louise: Oh.

11:10.330 --> 11:11.540
[ Brakes squeal ]

11:11.540 --> 11:14.000
This is not good.

11:14.000 --> 11:16.460
Not good.

11:16.460 --> 11:18.080
Oh.

11:18.080 --> 11:19.620
I'm sorry
the energy burst

11:19.620 --> 11:21.460
didn't conveniently happen
next to a highway.

11:21.460 --> 11:24.620
I -- I mean,
we could look at a map.

11:24.620 --> 11:27.580
Okay. I'll just be a --
just be a second.

11:27.580 --> 11:29.750
[ Sighs ]

11:29.750 --> 11:31.580
Let's see where we are.

11:31.580 --> 11:32.670
Hmm.

11:32.670 --> 11:34.920
Of course
I know where we are.

11:34.920 --> 11:37.580
It's right
in the middle of nowhere.

11:37.580 --> 11:40.540
Why did I
bring my parents up?

11:40.540 --> 11:42.670
I brought them up because,
when you became king,

11:42.670 --> 11:44.500
you said you never wanted to be
like your own parents,

11:44.500 --> 11:46.290
like any other king
before you.

11:46.290 --> 11:48.460
I'm reminding you
that you promised me

11:48.460 --> 11:49.620
that you would be
more understanding.

11:52.500 --> 11:54.750
Yes, he hurt me,

11:54.750 --> 11:56.670
and there's a part of me
that wants him to pay for that,

11:56.670 --> 11:59.290
but we have to be bigger
than that.

11:59.290 --> 12:01.710
So, to answer
your question, no.

12:01.710 --> 12:02.960
No, we don't
just let him walk away.

12:02.960 --> 12:05.080
We give him a fair trial.

12:05.080 --> 12:07.380
We let the people decide.

12:07.380 --> 12:11.750
♪♪

12:11.750 --> 12:15.500
[ Breathes deeply ]

12:15.500 --> 12:17.830
Look.

12:17.830 --> 12:19.330
♪♪

12:19.330 --> 12:21.920
I am not trying
to protect Maximus.

12:21.920 --> 12:24.210
I am trying
to protect you.

12:27.580 --> 12:29.210
From yourself.

12:29.210 --> 12:32.040
Guys! Got it!
Good to go.

12:32.040 --> 12:33.500
Yep.

12:33.500 --> 12:39.040
♪♪

12:39.040 --> 12:40.580
Maximus:
Should the Royals return,

12:40.580 --> 12:43.330
I want to make sure
we have every plan in place

12:43.330 --> 12:45.330
to stop them
from getting to me.

12:45.330 --> 12:49.210
My King, if I might have a word
with you...privately.

12:51.960 --> 12:54.000
Guards, give us a moment.

12:56.290 --> 12:58.880
I'm hearing rumors
of a rebel group

12:58.880 --> 13:01.290
that are planning an attempt
on your life.

13:01.290 --> 13:02.830
Why do you do this?

13:02.830 --> 13:04.670
My King, for --
for your protection.

13:04.670 --> 13:05.790
I don't believe it.

13:05.790 --> 13:07.830
The people are happy.

13:07.830 --> 13:10.460
At this time,
we must take every precaution.

13:14.880 --> 13:16.670
♪♪

13:16.670 --> 13:18.250
Where did you hear
this rumor?

13:18.250 --> 13:21.210
A concerned citizen, uh,
brought it to my attention.

13:21.210 --> 13:23.170
He requested
to remain anonymous.

13:23.170 --> 13:24.880
Well, if this is true,

13:24.880 --> 13:26.880
we should bring the guards in
to hear this.

13:26.880 --> 13:29.420
I disagree.

13:29.420 --> 13:31.210
Why?

13:31.210 --> 13:33.080
Why should we trust
the Royal Guard

13:33.080 --> 13:34.750
more than anyone else?

13:34.750 --> 13:39.170
There is a conspiracy
against you.

13:39.170 --> 13:41.290
What do you suggest?

13:41.290 --> 13:43.000
♪♪

13:43.000 --> 13:45.960
You and I handle this,
alone.

13:45.960 --> 13:47.210
Use the twins
in the control room,

13:47.210 --> 13:48.830
search Attilan
for these rebels.

13:48.830 --> 13:50.670
We find them,
we detain them,

13:50.670 --> 13:52.580
we force them to tell us
who is involved,

13:52.580 --> 13:54.580
and then we make an example
of them.

13:54.580 --> 13:57.670
♪♪

13:57.670 --> 14:00.330
[ Breathes sharply ]

14:00.330 --> 14:02.920
The way my family has treated me
over the years,

14:02.920 --> 14:05.000
the lack of respect,

14:05.000 --> 14:06.960
has bled over,
infecting others.

14:06.960 --> 14:08.170
♪♪

14:08.170 --> 14:09.420
[ Scoffs ]

14:09.420 --> 14:11.040
I should've
seen this coming.

14:11.040 --> 14:12.960
Find out what you can.

14:12.960 --> 14:14.540
Meet me
in the control room.

14:14.540 --> 14:16.290
I will.

14:16.290 --> 14:17.880
They always
underestimate me.

14:17.880 --> 14:18.960
What's that?

14:18.960 --> 14:21.380
Nothing.

14:21.380 --> 14:23.290
Go on.

14:23.290 --> 14:32.210
♪♪

14:32.210 --> 14:34.040
Again.

14:34.040 --> 14:36.920
[ Both grunting ]

14:36.920 --> 14:40.040
[ Breathing heavily ]

14:40.040 --> 14:42.000
This technique
doesn't work.

14:42.000 --> 14:43.120
Well, it's worked
for all Inhumans.

14:43.120 --> 14:45.000
It should work for you.

14:45.000 --> 14:46.920
[ Panting ]

14:46.920 --> 14:49.250
I don't see why I have to learn
any of this, anyway.

14:49.250 --> 14:53.580
I'm part of the Royal Family.
I have guards and you.

14:53.580 --> 14:56.830
Mm. And what about that day
that you have neither?

14:56.830 --> 14:58.380
[ Chuckles ]

14:58.380 --> 14:59.790
Again.

14:59.790 --> 15:03.750
[ Both grunting ]

15:03.750 --> 15:06.580
Now, this training
is not about today or tomorrow.

15:06.580 --> 15:09.790
It's for the day that
you least expect to use it.

15:09.790 --> 15:11.500
Now, if you're
the last man standing,

15:11.500 --> 15:13.620
how will you
protect yourself?

15:13.620 --> 15:14.540
Or Attilan?

15:14.540 --> 15:16.000
Karnak: Gorgon...

15:17.540 --> 15:18.620
...easy.

15:25.620 --> 15:28.670
At least let me fight with
someone I stand a chance with.

15:28.670 --> 15:30.380
No.

15:31.790 --> 15:33.790
You have to be smarter
and more cunning

15:33.790 --> 15:35.380
than anyone in Attilan.

15:35.380 --> 15:36.500
It's the only way
you'll survive.

15:36.500 --> 15:39.750
Medusa, even little Crystal,
are skilled fighters.

15:39.750 --> 15:41.960
It's part of who we are.

15:41.960 --> 15:45.040
Even your brother
has subjected himself to this,

15:45.040 --> 15:46.380
and he has
the most powerful --

15:46.380 --> 15:47.670
Powerful weapon in Attilan,
yeah.

15:47.670 --> 15:49.790
How many times
do I need to hear that?

15:49.790 --> 15:52.000
You haven't heard it,
or else you wouldn't be here.

15:59.920 --> 16:01.380
[ Scoffs ]

16:01.380 --> 16:03.040
That's enough embarrassment
for today.

16:06.790 --> 16:08.920
[ Sighs ]

16:08.920 --> 16:10.710
He'll never learn.

16:10.710 --> 16:14.580
♪♪

16:14.580 --> 16:16.080
Aah!

16:16.080 --> 16:18.420
[ Groaning ]

16:18.420 --> 16:19.710
[ Groaning ]

16:19.710 --> 16:21.750
Gorgon, calm! Calm.

16:21.750 --> 16:24.080
A sneak attack
makes you --
Smarter.

16:24.080 --> 16:27.380
And...more cunning.

16:27.380 --> 16:29.580
You're an excellent teacher,
Gorgon.

16:29.580 --> 16:30.920
Thank you.

16:30.920 --> 16:39.540
♪♪

16:39.540 --> 16:42.920
♪♪

16:42.920 --> 16:44.420
[ Insects chirping ]

16:44.420 --> 16:46.290
I can still smell the mines
on them.

16:46.290 --> 16:47.750
We're soldiers now.

16:47.750 --> 16:50.250
Let's hope.

16:50.250 --> 16:52.380
The Royals don't know
you're here.

16:52.380 --> 16:54.880
When they attack,
we'll draw them in,

16:54.880 --> 16:55.790
then you'll surround them.

16:55.790 --> 16:57.670
Move out.

16:57.670 --> 16:59.460
♪♪

16:59.460 --> 17:02.540
Be careful!
Stay out of our way.

17:02.540 --> 17:03.880
Mordis:
Especially my way.

17:03.880 --> 17:06.290
I'd hate to fry
your tender bodies.

17:06.290 --> 17:10.420
♪♪

17:10.420 --> 17:12.040
You're the
one who should be worried

17:12.040 --> 17:13.790
about living
through this.

17:13.790 --> 17:14.620
I have no worries.

17:14.620 --> 17:16.210
[ Scoffs ]

17:16.210 --> 17:18.500
Because you think
you can keep healing yourself.

17:18.500 --> 17:21.210
Have you ever had
a DNA test before?

17:21.210 --> 17:22.920
Get to the point.

17:22.920 --> 17:24.500
Your telomeres
are growing shorter.

17:24.500 --> 17:25.750
Meaning?

17:25.750 --> 17:26.880
Meaning
you may not be able

17:26.880 --> 17:29.500
to regenerate yourself
forever.

17:29.500 --> 17:32.620
One day, you'll die...

17:32.620 --> 17:33.880
and that's it.

17:33.880 --> 17:36.040
♪♪

17:36.040 --> 17:38.040
You're lying.

17:38.040 --> 17:42.420
♪ I was gonna die young ♪

17:42.420 --> 17:44.330
♪ Now I gotta wait for you,
honey ♪

17:44.330 --> 17:46.670
This is just about
the highest point on Oahu.

17:46.670 --> 17:48.080
It's beautiful up here.

17:48.080 --> 17:50.960
♪ Now I gotta wait for you,
honey ♪

17:50.960 --> 17:53.080
Have you ever been to
the other side of the water?

17:53.080 --> 17:54.460
♪ Now I gotta wait for you,
honey ♪

17:54.460 --> 17:59.210
No, I've never left
the island.

17:59.210 --> 18:01.580
I've never been
outside Attilan.

18:01.580 --> 18:03.250
I never imagined
it would be like this.

18:03.250 --> 18:05.500
Maybe after
we find your family,

18:05.500 --> 18:08.250
we can take a trip
somewhere together.

18:08.250 --> 18:10.790
♪ I could've missed it ♪

18:10.790 --> 18:12.580
♪ I never knew ♪

18:12.580 --> 18:13.920
Should we give it a try?

18:13.920 --> 18:15.750
♪ Chain reaction,
but you're holding the fuse ♪

18:15.750 --> 18:17.170
Okay.

18:17.170 --> 18:20.500
♪ I was gonna die young ♪

18:20.500 --> 18:23.120
You might want
to step back.
Good idea.

18:23.120 --> 18:27.330
♪ Now I gotta wait for you,
honey ♪

18:27.330 --> 18:32.250
♪ Now I gotta wait for you,
honey ♪

18:32.250 --> 18:34.960
♪ Now I gotta wait for you,
honey ♪

18:34.960 --> 18:36.250
[ Thunder rumbles ]

18:36.250 --> 18:38.580
[ Thunder crashes ]

18:38.580 --> 18:40.330
♪♪

18:40.330 --> 18:41.540
[ Thunder crashes ]

18:41.540 --> 18:42.960
[ Brakes squeal ]

18:42.960 --> 18:44.670
[ Engine shuts off ]

18:44.670 --> 18:46.540
Sorry. I got to
check the map again.

18:46.540 --> 18:48.250
[ Thunder rumbles ]

18:48.250 --> 18:49.750
Well, if you
don't mind my asking,

18:49.750 --> 18:51.960
why do you guys live
on the far side of the Moon?

18:51.960 --> 18:53.040
I mean,
why hide like that?

18:55.210 --> 18:57.500
Me?

18:57.500 --> 18:58.790
You guys are hiding
from me?

18:58.790 --> 19:01.120
We used to live on Earth
for generations,

19:01.120 --> 19:02.540
and as you might know,
humans,

19:02.540 --> 19:05.210
when they meet something
that they don't understand,

19:05.210 --> 19:08.710
their first reaction
is to attack.

19:08.710 --> 19:12.580
So we...
left for our own safety.

19:12.580 --> 19:14.500
Ours and yours.

19:14.500 --> 19:16.960
[ Thunder crashes ]

19:16.960 --> 19:20.330
Huh. That's weird.

19:20.330 --> 19:22.250
But back to what
you were saying, though.

19:22.250 --> 19:25.420
Uh, yes, there are
bad people on Earth,

19:25.420 --> 19:27.920
but I would say
most are good.

19:27.920 --> 19:29.750
I mean, what if I thought
that everyone on Attilan

19:29.750 --> 19:30.960
was like your Maximus?

19:30.960 --> 19:32.710
That's a really good point.
Uh, where are we?

19:32.710 --> 19:34.210
Oh, um...

19:34.210 --> 19:35.380
[ Thunder rumbles ]

19:35.380 --> 19:36.920
It looks like we're here.

19:36.920 --> 19:39.420
She could've landed
within a couple miles of here.

19:39.420 --> 19:41.000
Any direction, really.

19:41.000 --> 19:42.420
And then she could've moved on
from there.

19:42.420 --> 19:43.830
Yeah.

19:43.830 --> 19:45.790
[ Thunder crashes ]

19:45.790 --> 19:48.330
They say lightning
never strikes twice.

19:49.120 --> 19:50.500
It's Crystal.

19:50.500 --> 19:51.920
♪♪

19:57.460 --> 19:58.790
You have Royal Guards
around you at all times.

19:58.790 --> 20:01.120
Why worry about rebels?

20:01.120 --> 20:03.500
I'm not truly worried
about them, Bronaja.

20:03.500 --> 20:06.330
I'm worried about what
the revolt will do to Attilan.

20:06.330 --> 20:07.670
And who started this?

20:07.670 --> 20:11.580
Was it the Genetic Council
or a Black Bolt sympathizer...

20:11.580 --> 20:14.960
[ Scoffs ]
Was it Tibor?

20:14.960 --> 20:17.670
You said you trusted him.

20:17.670 --> 20:19.380
And me.

20:19.380 --> 20:20.920
Trusting someone

20:20.920 --> 20:22.170
and that person
being trustworthy

20:22.170 --> 20:24.620
are two different things.

20:24.620 --> 20:27.000
[ Grunts ]

20:27.000 --> 20:29.040
Tell me --
what do you see?

20:29.040 --> 20:31.000
[ Grunts ]

20:31.000 --> 20:32.420
[ Breathes sharply ]

20:32.420 --> 20:33.620
What?

20:33.620 --> 20:35.000
I-I saw you and Tibor.

20:35.000 --> 20:36.330
And?

20:36.330 --> 20:39.000
You were talking --
just talking.

20:39.000 --> 20:40.620
What were we talking
about?

20:40.620 --> 20:42.000
I don't know.

20:42.000 --> 20:44.710
Were we happy or angry?

20:44.710 --> 20:46.460
Happy, I guess.

20:46.460 --> 20:49.250
Were we laughing?

20:49.250 --> 20:50.500
Dancing, perhaps?

20:50.500 --> 20:51.880
What? No.

20:51.880 --> 20:53.080
Then how do you know
we were happy?

20:53.080 --> 20:54.670
I-I-I don't know.

20:54.670 --> 20:56.830
You only gave me two choices,
and you didn't seem angry.

20:56.830 --> 20:58.750
♪♪

20:58.750 --> 21:01.000
[ Sighs ]

21:01.000 --> 21:03.750
I'm pushing you too hard.

21:03.750 --> 21:05.460
I know.

21:05.460 --> 21:07.750
You must be very worried
about your father.

21:07.750 --> 21:10.120
♪♪

21:10.120 --> 21:11.750
Yes.

21:11.750 --> 21:14.210
I am.

21:14.210 --> 21:15.540
[ Sighs ]

21:15.540 --> 21:20.380
Your father is a soldier
embarking on a great cause.

21:20.380 --> 21:23.420
He will literally
open the gates of Paradise

21:23.420 --> 21:25.540
for the rest of us.

21:25.540 --> 21:28.250
You do want him
to come home safely, don't you?

21:28.250 --> 21:30.330
Yes.

21:30.330 --> 21:31.920
Of course.

21:31.920 --> 21:33.830
Then let's try again.

21:33.830 --> 21:35.750
Was there anything
in your vision that suggests

21:35.750 --> 21:38.040
I should be concerned
about Tibor?

21:38.040 --> 21:39.420
♪♪

21:39.420 --> 21:42.540
I...

21:42.540 --> 21:44.380
I think you can trust him.

21:44.380 --> 21:47.960
♪♪

21:47.960 --> 21:49.790
Good.

21:49.790 --> 21:52.290
Thank you.

21:52.290 --> 21:56.330
I want you with me
when I meet him.

21:56.330 --> 21:59.620
Didn't he want you
to go alone?

21:59.620 --> 22:01.620
Your importance to me
grows daily.

22:01.620 --> 22:05.330
♪♪

22:05.330 --> 22:07.540
I want you to see things
from the inside.

22:07.540 --> 22:09.620
♪♪

22:09.620 --> 22:11.460
Thank you.

22:11.460 --> 22:16.750
♪♪

22:20.290 --> 22:26.290
Auran, Flora, Mordis.

22:26.290 --> 22:27.500
Very good stuff.

22:27.500 --> 22:28.790
Yeah.

22:28.790 --> 22:30.290
Seems hardly fair.

22:31.750 --> 22:33.620
There was a time
I would've chastised you

22:33.620 --> 22:35.290
for being so cocky.

22:35.290 --> 22:37.080
But?

22:42.380 --> 22:44.670
I think
I might've been harsh,

22:44.670 --> 22:47.170
'cause I leaned too much
on my gift.

22:47.170 --> 22:49.000
Yeah, well,
that's what I always said.

22:50.580 --> 22:52.750
The --
The flaw in my thinking

22:52.750 --> 22:55.460
was that there's only one way
to do things.

22:55.460 --> 22:57.670
Your way.

22:57.670 --> 22:59.500
Yeah.

22:59.500 --> 23:07.960
♪♪

23:07.960 --> 23:13.880
♪♪

23:13.880 --> 23:16.210
This new and improved
Karnak,

23:16.210 --> 23:18.330
how would he get us
inside this building

23:18.330 --> 23:20.710
without getting
the humans killed?

23:20.710 --> 23:24.080
Auran could be
in any one of those windows,

23:24.080 --> 23:26.170
armed...

23:26.170 --> 23:27.790
sniping us
before we make it across.

23:27.790 --> 23:30.540
I can't...see the flaw.

23:30.540 --> 23:33.540
Ah.

23:33.540 --> 23:35.710
Well, I'm seeing the one flaw
that you're not seeing.

23:35.710 --> 23:38.040
♪♪

23:38.040 --> 23:40.540
I can't wait to hear this.
Good.

23:40.540 --> 23:43.080
Now, Auran and her people
don't know that you're broken.

23:43.080 --> 23:45.580
And they think that
the almighty Karnak

23:45.580 --> 23:46.830
is gonna be heading
their way.

23:46.830 --> 23:48.290
So give them
what they expect.

23:48.290 --> 23:52.460
Now, there is no flaw,
if they don't know there is one.

23:52.460 --> 23:54.120
♪♪

23:54.120 --> 23:55.670
I'm -- I'm impressed.

23:55.670 --> 23:58.170
[ Laughs ]

23:58.170 --> 24:02.710
♪♪

24:02.710 --> 24:05.080
Let me make this
a little bit easier.

24:05.080 --> 24:13.000
♪♪

24:13.000 --> 24:22.960
♪♪

24:22.960 --> 24:24.620
Well...

24:24.620 --> 24:26.790
♪♪

24:26.790 --> 24:28.420
[ Door creaks ]

24:28.420 --> 24:30.420
[ Breathes deeply ]

24:30.420 --> 24:32.250
[ Electricity crackles ]

24:32.250 --> 24:36.290
[ Electricity powers down ]

24:36.290 --> 24:38.670
♪♪

24:38.670 --> 24:40.000
They're here.

24:40.000 --> 24:42.120
Well, you don't say.

24:42.120 --> 24:44.620
Keep on eye
on Declan here.

24:44.620 --> 24:46.710
Aye, aye.

24:46.710 --> 24:48.580
♪♪

24:48.580 --> 24:50.330
Flora:
It's Karnak.

24:50.330 --> 24:54.290
Shoot him.

24:54.290 --> 24:56.670
The others are probably
out there, as well.

24:56.670 --> 24:58.000
Why are you waiting?

24:58.000 --> 25:00.120
No, it doesn't make sense.
He wants me to shoot him.

25:00.120 --> 25:01.460
It's got to be a trick.

25:01.460 --> 25:03.380
Please don't shoot me...
please don't shoot me...

25:03.380 --> 25:06.330
Tell Mordis
Karnak is coming -- now.

25:06.330 --> 25:13.040
♪♪

25:13.040 --> 25:21.210
♪♪

25:21.210 --> 25:23.210
Hi, Auran.

25:23.210 --> 25:28.710
♪♪

25:28.710 --> 25:30.710
[ Door opens, closes ]

25:30.710 --> 25:33.670
♪♪

25:33.670 --> 25:37.500
Look who I found.

25:37.500 --> 25:45.250
♪♪

25:45.250 --> 25:46.710
Karnak is coming.

25:46.710 --> 25:49.710
♪♪

25:49.710 --> 25:52.250
Mm.

25:52.250 --> 25:53.830
Around that corner.

25:53.830 --> 25:55.170
Go get him.

25:55.170 --> 25:56.580
♪♪

25:56.580 --> 25:58.920
This will be over
in a second.

25:58.920 --> 26:00.830
Psst!
I'm over here.

26:00.830 --> 26:08.710
♪♪

26:08.710 --> 26:11.210
♪♪

26:11.210 --> 26:12.500
Psst!

26:12.500 --> 26:14.120
Aah!

26:14.120 --> 26:19.120
♪♪

26:19.120 --> 26:21.170
I hope that didn't hurt
your little hand!

26:23.170 --> 26:25.920
Dear, dear Mordis...

26:25.920 --> 26:28.000
It's been a long time.

26:28.000 --> 26:32.170
The all-powerful Karnak.
Hiding, are we?

26:32.170 --> 26:35.750
I've heard that
you like to tell your enemies

26:35.750 --> 26:38.290
all the different ways
that you could defeat them,

26:38.290 --> 26:43.080
so I'm gonna give you
the chance to do so right now.

26:43.080 --> 26:46.250
Please...

26:46.250 --> 26:49.120
show me your genius.

26:49.120 --> 26:51.120
Do you remember
the first day

26:51.120 --> 26:52.960
you came out
of Terrigenesis?

26:52.960 --> 26:56.790
So scared, so alone.

26:56.790 --> 26:59.500
Literally,
the face of death.

26:59.500 --> 27:02.120
How many did you harm
that day?

27:02.120 --> 27:05.830
How horrible
you must have felt.

27:05.830 --> 27:07.380
I didn't ask for this gift.

27:07.380 --> 27:08.750
It's not what I wanted.

27:08.750 --> 27:11.420
That's exactly
what I told the Genetic Council,

27:11.420 --> 27:12.920
but they didn't care.

27:12.920 --> 27:15.210
They wanted
to put you down.

27:15.210 --> 27:18.080
How I pleaded
for your life.

27:18.080 --> 27:20.040
Black Bolt
was just as dangerous,

27:20.040 --> 27:23.670
but he was given far more
opportunities than I was.

27:23.670 --> 27:25.540
I was immediately locked
in that cell!

27:25.540 --> 27:27.040
But that's
what kept you alive.

27:27.040 --> 27:29.920
No! Being locked away
is not being alive.

27:29.920 --> 27:31.380
Yeah, you're right.

27:31.380 --> 27:35.000
Mistakes were made,
but that was then.

27:35.000 --> 27:40.960
Maybe, from this moment forward,
things can be different.

27:40.960 --> 27:43.620
What happened to me,
that wasn't necessary.

27:43.620 --> 27:44.790
There were other options.

27:44.790 --> 27:47.540
♪♪

27:47.540 --> 27:48.920
Karnak!

27:48.920 --> 27:50.540
Over here.

27:50.540 --> 27:57.620
♪♪

27:57.620 --> 28:01.790
♪♪

28:01.790 --> 28:04.420
Got him.

28:04.420 --> 28:06.670
Karnak: For now.

28:11.580 --> 28:12.620
Who are you?

28:12.620 --> 28:13.790
Shh. Gorgon. And you?

28:13.790 --> 28:15.830
Sammy.

28:15.830 --> 28:17.540
Where's the quiet guy?

28:17.540 --> 28:19.960
Black Bolt and his wife
are safe.

28:19.960 --> 28:21.210
Hey, you need
to get out of here.

28:21.210 --> 28:22.250
Out there, to the left.

28:22.250 --> 28:23.380
I can help you.

28:23.380 --> 28:24.620
We got it covered.

28:24.620 --> 28:26.540
Leave now so we don't
have to worry about you.

28:26.540 --> 28:29.290
♪♪

28:29.290 --> 28:31.500
Are all of you
like Black Bolt?

28:31.500 --> 28:32.960
Do you all have powers?

28:32.960 --> 28:34.750
Sure as hell do.

28:34.750 --> 28:36.500
So I'm not a freak.

28:36.500 --> 28:39.250
You're not a freak.

28:39.250 --> 28:44.040
Tell...Black Bolt thanks.

28:44.040 --> 28:45.330
[ Footsteps ]

28:45.330 --> 28:47.580
The story
that you told Mordis --

28:47.580 --> 28:49.040
is it true?

28:49.040 --> 28:50.790
[ Scoffs ]
Are you kidding?

28:50.790 --> 28:52.580
When he walked out
of the Terrigenesis chamber,

28:52.580 --> 28:54.170
it scared
the bejesus out of me.

28:54.170 --> 28:56.000
I wanted to put him down
right then and there.

28:56.000 --> 28:57.580
Just trying to stall him.

28:57.580 --> 28:58.960
[ Chuckles ]

28:58.960 --> 29:01.460
Okay.
What's the plan now?

29:01.460 --> 29:03.830
Auran is mine.

29:03.830 --> 29:05.540
She has a gun.

29:05.540 --> 29:07.290
♪♪

29:07.290 --> 29:09.580
Who needs guns
when you've got hooves?

29:09.580 --> 29:11.330
♪♪

29:11.330 --> 29:13.000
Hold it.

29:13.000 --> 29:19.120
♪♪

29:19.120 --> 29:27.620
♪♪

29:27.620 --> 29:28.500
[ Footsteps
approaching rapidly ]

29:28.500 --> 29:31.250
♪♪

29:31.250 --> 29:33.670
[ Gasps ]

29:33.670 --> 29:34.750
Loyolis, right?

29:34.750 --> 29:36.210
What?

29:36.210 --> 29:39.250
We met at your son
and daughter's Terrigenesis.

29:39.250 --> 29:40.500
[ Gasps ]

29:40.500 --> 29:41.620
Relax. You're gonna sleep

29:41.620 --> 29:44.250
and wake up
with a slight headache.

29:44.250 --> 29:45.750
[ Body thuds ]

29:45.750 --> 29:48.080
♪♪

29:53.710 --> 29:56.380
Gorgon: Hello, Auran.

29:56.380 --> 29:58.920
I'm surprised
you've come back for more.

29:58.920 --> 30:00.960
Didn't go so well for you
last time.

30:00.960 --> 30:02.380
Yeah, well,
I have a pretty good feeling

30:02.380 --> 30:04.120
how this
will all turn out.

30:05.290 --> 30:06.670
Hyah!

30:06.670 --> 30:09.170
[ Both grunting ]

30:09.170 --> 30:16.960
♪♪

30:16.960 --> 30:19.170
Aah!

30:19.170 --> 30:22.620
♪♪

30:22.620 --> 30:24.580
Come on!
Where's the fight in you?!

30:24.580 --> 30:27.920
[ Techno music plays ]

30:27.920 --> 30:40.330
♪♪

30:40.330 --> 30:42.040
Now would be a good time
to surrender.

30:42.040 --> 30:43.330
No.

30:44.790 --> 30:46.120
[ Gasps ]

30:46.120 --> 30:51.170
♪♪

30:51.170 --> 30:52.830
I surrender.

30:52.830 --> 30:56.080
♪♪

30:56.080 --> 30:57.250
Karnak:
I assume you're Declan.

30:58.830 --> 31:01.620
I am.
And you're Karnak?

31:01.620 --> 31:04.120
♪♪

31:04.120 --> 31:08.290
Just -- Please just tell me --
exactly who is Maximus?

31:08.290 --> 31:12.790
Traitor brother
of our King, Black Bolt.

31:12.790 --> 31:15.000
♪♪

31:15.000 --> 31:19.210
So that's why Maximus
wanted me to kill him.

31:19.210 --> 31:21.170
How do you know Maximus?

31:21.170 --> 31:23.000
He -- He paid
for all this research.

31:23.000 --> 31:24.960
Let's continue this outside.

31:24.960 --> 31:26.380
No, wait!
I need my briefcase.

31:26.380 --> 31:27.380
You'll get it later.

31:27.380 --> 31:28.580
No.

31:28.580 --> 31:30.420
Ah. It's got my research.

31:30.420 --> 31:32.920
♪♪

31:32.920 --> 31:34.460
[ Horns honking in distance ]

31:34.460 --> 31:37.500
So, now we just wait?

31:37.500 --> 31:39.040
Now we wait.

31:42.080 --> 31:45.120
So...

31:45.120 --> 31:47.960
will you be happy
to get home?

31:47.960 --> 31:49.960
Absolutely.

31:49.960 --> 31:51.330
I won't.

31:51.330 --> 31:54.040
I mean, I'll be happy
for you, of course.

31:54.040 --> 31:56.620
But...it's hard to believe

31:56.620 --> 31:58.710
I've only known you
for a little while.

31:58.710 --> 32:01.420
I thought being on Earth
would be horrible,

32:01.420 --> 32:02.670
but it's...

32:02.670 --> 32:03.540
Great?

32:03.540 --> 32:05.500
Yeah.

32:05.500 --> 32:08.670
[ Chuckling ] Great.

32:08.670 --> 32:10.790
What if they didn't see
the signal?

32:10.790 --> 32:12.620
♪♪

32:12.620 --> 32:14.790
[ Laughing ]
Are you kidding?

32:14.790 --> 32:16.960
That was
impossible to miss.

32:16.960 --> 32:20.170
I mean,
that was so, so awesome.

32:20.170 --> 32:23.210
You're like
some kind of god of thunder.

32:23.210 --> 32:26.710
♪♪

32:26.710 --> 32:30.170
♪ La la la ♪

32:30.170 --> 32:31.710
You kissed me.

32:31.710 --> 32:33.710
Yeah.

32:33.710 --> 32:39.460
♪♪

32:39.460 --> 32:41.540
Hello, little sister.

32:41.540 --> 32:43.120
Medusa! [ Laughs ]

32:43.120 --> 32:45.120
-Black Bolt, you're here.
-Oh!

32:45.120 --> 32:46.830
I was so worried
about you.

32:46.830 --> 32:48.330
I'm good. I'm okay.

32:48.330 --> 32:50.210
We got your signal.

32:50.210 --> 32:52.460
And I see that
you made a friend.

32:52.460 --> 32:55.120
A, uh, human friend.

32:55.120 --> 32:56.620
Uh, hi. I'm Dave.

32:56.620 --> 32:59.750
♪♪

32:59.750 --> 33:01.460
Dave helped me find you.

33:01.460 --> 33:04.120
He's the only reason
we were able to find each other.

33:04.120 --> 33:05.580
He's a good person.

33:05.580 --> 33:08.670
See? Earth is filled
with good people.

33:08.670 --> 33:11.120
Uh, this is, uh --
This is Louise.

33:11.120 --> 33:14.750
We, uh --
We also made a friend.

33:17.790 --> 33:19.580
Where's Lockjaw?

33:19.580 --> 33:21.170
He's resting
back at Dave's barn.

33:23.080 --> 33:26.040
We need Lockjaw
to get Karnak and Gorgon.

33:29.460 --> 33:31.420
And then,
we can go home.

33:31.420 --> 33:35.790
♪♪

33:35.790 --> 33:38.080
We better
tie that one up.

33:40.580 --> 33:42.120
What happens
when we return home

33:42.120 --> 33:44.710
and you see the people prefer
Maximus as King of Attilan?

33:44.710 --> 33:46.580
We'll find out
soon enough.

33:50.960 --> 33:53.330
[ Groans ]

33:53.330 --> 33:54.620
Wh-What happened?

33:54.620 --> 33:56.170
You lost, loser.

33:56.170 --> 33:57.920
[ Groans ]
Now we go home.

33:57.920 --> 34:00.250
None of this was necessary,
Karnak.

34:00.250 --> 34:02.000
But no one's gonna
lock me away again.

34:02.000 --> 34:05.210
-He'll kill us all!
-No! Everyone, go!

34:05.210 --> 34:07.330
-No! Don't take me back!
-Go!

34:07.330 --> 34:08.580
I'm not getting
locked away!

34:08.580 --> 34:10.420
Go!

34:10.420 --> 34:11.580
Aah!

34:11.580 --> 34:15.040
Aaaaah!

34:15.040 --> 34:17.710
[ Rumbling, crashing ]

34:17.710 --> 34:19.830
[ Metal creaks ]

34:19.830 --> 34:23.460
[ Metal creaking ]

34:26.120 --> 34:28.120
[ Rumbling ]

34:33.330 --> 34:35.920
[ Brakes squeal ]

34:35.920 --> 34:37.420
[ Engines shut off ]

34:37.420 --> 34:39.880
♪♪

34:39.880 --> 34:41.880
[ Insects chirping ]

34:41.880 --> 34:43.210
Lockjaw's in here.

34:43.210 --> 34:47.750
♪♪

34:47.750 --> 34:49.290
[ Door creaks ]

34:49.290 --> 34:52.460
[ Lockjaw barks ]

34:52.460 --> 34:53.460
Come on, boy!

34:53.460 --> 34:54.920
[ Lockjaw barks ]

34:54.920 --> 34:57.290
♪♪

34:57.290 --> 34:58.750
Good boy.

34:58.750 --> 35:00.710
Wow.

35:00.710 --> 35:03.170
Oh, wow.

35:03.170 --> 35:05.580
He's so big.

35:05.580 --> 35:08.460
I cannot wait
for him to take us the Moon.

35:08.460 --> 35:10.380
[ Lockjaw whines ]

35:10.380 --> 35:13.540
[ Lockjaw panting ]

35:13.540 --> 35:15.170
Let me talk to her.

35:15.170 --> 35:19.460
[ Siren wails ]

35:19.460 --> 35:21.880
Why are the police here?

35:21.880 --> 35:23.170
I'm driving a stolen car.

35:25.460 --> 35:26.790
Crystal, we need to go.

35:26.790 --> 35:29.250
Louise.
Wait.

35:29.250 --> 35:31.040
Just stay in here.

35:31.040 --> 35:33.670
♪♪

35:33.670 --> 35:35.380
[ Car door opens ]

35:35.380 --> 35:38.960
♪♪

35:38.960 --> 35:40.420
Audrey,
what's the matter?

35:40.420 --> 35:42.670
He's in the barn
with an alien named Crystal.

35:42.670 --> 35:44.290
Audrey,
what are you talking about?
Don't play dumb.

35:44.290 --> 35:46.250
Look, no, I --
I brought them here

35:46.250 --> 35:49.040
so they can just meet Lockjaw
and your friend Crystal.

35:49.040 --> 35:51.170
I -- You've just been
so wrapped up in her.

35:51.170 --> 35:54.420
I mean, what if this is some
kind of -- of danger or threat?

35:54.420 --> 35:57.120
Sir, we're gonna need
to see inside that barn.

35:57.120 --> 35:58.620
She is definitely
the kind of human

35:58.620 --> 35:59.880
you guys
were talking about.

36:01.790 --> 36:04.540
I'm sorry, Crystal.
we have to go.

36:04.540 --> 36:05.710
Dave...

36:05.710 --> 36:08.330
Louise, I need your help
one more time.

36:08.330 --> 36:09.750
Y-Yeah, I --

36:09.750 --> 36:11.380
Yep, I get it.

36:11.380 --> 36:13.500
You need me
to handle the police.

36:13.500 --> 36:15.290
I am sorry.

36:15.290 --> 36:20.380
♪♪

36:20.380 --> 36:27.920
♪♪

36:27.920 --> 36:32.620
♪♪

36:32.620 --> 36:35.080
She told us
there's an alien dog in there.

36:35.080 --> 36:36.580
I want to see
an alien dog.

36:36.580 --> 36:38.080
Audrey, no.

36:38.080 --> 36:40.040
[ Door creaks ]

36:41.880 --> 36:44.000
Oh, thank goodness.

36:44.000 --> 36:45.120
Ma'am, are you okay?

36:45.120 --> 36:46.250
I am now.

36:46.250 --> 36:47.830
This one
locked me in here.

36:47.830 --> 36:49.670
Can someone tell us
what's going on here?

36:49.670 --> 36:52.790
She and Dave used to date --
until he dumped her for me.

36:52.790 --> 36:54.540
Oh, my God, no.

36:54.540 --> 36:58.000
No, Officer, that's not true.
That's not true at all.

36:58.000 --> 37:00.290
Audrey,
I'm really sorry,

37:00.290 --> 37:01.880
but you're gonna
have to back off.

37:01.880 --> 37:03.500
We're gonna walk away now.

37:03.500 --> 37:07.120
If this happens again,
you're gonna have a problem.

37:07.120 --> 37:09.670
No, wait, please!
You have to believe me!

37:09.670 --> 37:11.080
Audrey, just stop.

37:11.080 --> 37:12.330
Officer,
they're still out there!

37:12.330 --> 37:13.750
They could be dangerous!

37:13.750 --> 37:15.670
That dog was huge!

37:15.670 --> 37:23.000
♪♪

37:23.000 --> 37:25.290
[ Car doors open, close ]

37:25.290 --> 37:27.710
[ Engine starts ]

37:27.710 --> 37:34.460
♪♪

37:34.460 --> 37:37.420
Gorgon? Karnak?

37:37.420 --> 37:39.380
[ Clattering ]

37:44.380 --> 37:46.620
[ Ruelle's "The Other Side"
plays ]

37:46.620 --> 37:49.290
[ Electricity crackles ]

37:49.290 --> 37:51.420
[ Glass shatters ]

37:51.420 --> 37:58.830
♪ I don't wanna know
who we are ♪

37:58.830 --> 38:06.210
♪ Without each other,
it's just too hard ♪

38:06.210 --> 38:14.380
♪ I don't wanna leave here
without you ♪

38:14.380 --> 38:16.670
I-I tried to get to him.

38:17.960 --> 38:19.460
He's gone.

38:19.460 --> 38:21.120
[ Shuddered breathing ]

38:21.120 --> 38:21.880
♪ I don't wanna know ♪

38:21.880 --> 38:23.750
Gorgon's dead.

38:23.750 --> 38:26.250
♪ I don't wanna know ♪

38:26.250 --> 38:27.960
♪♪

38:27.960 --> 38:30.380
♪ I don't wanna know ♪

38:30.380 --> 38:34.580
♪ I don't wanna know ♪

38:34.580 --> 38:37.290
♪ I don't wanna know ♪

38:37.290 --> 38:41.330
♪ I don't wanna know ♪

38:41.330 --> 38:45.380
♪ I don't wanna know ♪

38:45.380 --> 38:51.920
♪ We are buried
in broken dreams ♪

38:51.920 --> 38:58.250
♪ We are knee deep
without a plea ♪

38:58.250 --> 39:03.000
♪ Here without you ♪

39:03.000 --> 39:05.040
♪♪

39:12.210 --> 39:14.170
Maximus:
Tibor and his rebellious
friends here to kill me.

39:14.170 --> 39:17.420
But you should know
we have your families.

39:17.420 --> 39:21.330
If you resist,
we will kill them all.

39:21.330 --> 39:23.120
Put down your weapons.

39:23.120 --> 39:29.790
♪♪

39:29.790 --> 39:31.920
I am saddened that
so many of you

39:31.920 --> 39:35.080
followed Tibor
down this path of treachery.

39:35.080 --> 39:39.420
You will fail.

39:39.420 --> 39:40.960
You came after a king.

39:40.960 --> 39:44.040
-No!
-Please!

39:44.040 --> 39:47.250
Aah!

39:47.250 --> 39:48.710
You think I'm stupid.

39:48.710 --> 39:51.710
♪♪

39:51.710 --> 39:54.250
Is that
what you all think?

39:54.250 --> 39:56.790
That's I'm a stupid human?!

39:56.790 --> 40:00.500
That I can't tell
if someone is lying to my face?!

40:00.500 --> 40:03.420
Your arrogance
has blinded you!

40:03.420 --> 40:05.380
Nothing is going to stop me!

40:05.380 --> 40:07.540
Nothing!

40:07.540 --> 40:09.500
Take them away.

40:09.500 --> 40:12.420
♪♪

40:12.420 --> 40:15.880
Bronaja: What's
going to happen to them?

40:17.250 --> 40:19.620
What do you think?

40:21.460 --> 40:24.330
When you saw me
talking to Tibor,

40:24.330 --> 40:27.710
did he have a knife
in his hand?

40:27.710 --> 40:29.460
I don't know.

40:29.460 --> 40:31.000
Maybe.

40:31.000 --> 40:34.790
♪♪

40:34.790 --> 40:36.670
[ Sighs ]

40:36.670 --> 40:39.040
♪♪

40:39.040 --> 40:40.880
Why did you lie to me,
Bronaja?

40:40.880 --> 40:42.290
I'm sorry.

40:42.290 --> 40:43.830
[ Voice breaking ]
I-I was scared.

40:43.830 --> 40:46.620
I know fear.

40:46.620 --> 40:49.460
I do.

40:49.460 --> 40:50.960
It's a great motivator.

40:50.960 --> 40:52.960
But you have to understand

40:52.960 --> 40:55.920
that I'm trying to lead you
to something great.

40:55.920 --> 40:58.420
♪♪

40:58.420 --> 41:00.500
You do know that,
don't you?

41:00.500 --> 41:01.920
I do.

41:01.920 --> 41:12.250
♪♪

41:12.250 --> 41:17.080
I need you
to believe in me, Bronaja.

41:19.790 --> 41:22.080
Trust in me.

41:22.080 --> 41:26.420
I am the King of Attilan.

41:26.420 --> 41:29.000
Long live King Maximus.

41:29.000 --> 41:30.710
♪♪

41:30.710 --> 41:32.620
Say it.

41:32.620 --> 41:35.920
♪♪

41:35.920 --> 41:37.620
Say it.

41:37.620 --> 41:39.580
Long live King Maximus.

41:39.580 --> 41:45.460
♪♪

41:45.460 --> 41:47.120
There you go.

41:51.710 --> 42:02.710
♪♪

42:02.710 --> 42:11.540
♪♪

42:11.540 --> 42:20.170
♪♪
